OL,3,CNine-hour A&E nightmare robbed our two-
OL,4,Cyear-old son of a chance to survive
OL,6,FFinny was discharged at around 1am,
OL,7,Fbut hours later Liz woke up to find
OL,8,Fhim in the bed next to her, not
OL,9,Fbreathing.
OL,11,FHe had died from a twisted bowel
OL,12,Fcondition.
OL,14,FAn inquest found routine checks hadn't
OL,15,Fbeen carried out by hospital staff and
OL,16,Fthere were communication failures.
OL,18,FThe coroner said different hospital
OL,19,Fcare that night would have given Finny
OL,20,Fa chance of survival.
