OL,3,CNine-hour A&E nightmare robbed our two-
OL,4,Cyear-old son of a chance to survive
OL,6,F"He wasn't given a chance. He should
OL,7,Fhave been, because he was just two-
OL,8,Fyears-old, but there were a litany of
OL,9,Ffailures that meant that he was robbed
OL,10,Fof that chance," Liz tells me.
OL,12,FAs the government announces its ten-
OL,13,Fyear plan for the NHS, with the Prime
OL,14,FMinister pledging to "fundamentally re-
OL,15,Fwire" the health service, this family
OL,16,Fknows, all too well, that it must
OL,17,Fimprove.
OL,19,F"The system is flagrantly broken,"
OL,20,Fsays David.
