OL,3,CNine-hour A&E nightmare robbed our two-
OL,4,Cyear-old son of a chance to survive
OL,6,F"The problems with the NHS are really
OL,7,Fclear, for us they are beyond
OL,8,Fviscerally clear - something went
OL,9,Fcatastrophically wrong."
OL,11,FBut the couple are sceptical about the
OL,12,Fpromise to give patients "easier,
OL,13,Fquicker and more convenient care."
OL,15,F"It needs radical surgery," explains
OL,16,FDavid.
OL,18,F"It doesn't need performative little
OL,19,Ftricks around the edges, with some
OL,20,Fgeneric waffle about artificial
OL,21,Fintelligence sorting everything out.
